17:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Blue Prism and IFTTT share a solid foundation of core features including Visual Builder, Api Connections, Scheduling, Conditional Logic. Where Blue Prism pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Code Support and Error Handling and Team Collaboration, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on these capabilities. On the other hand, IFTTT uniquely offers Webhook Support, giving it an edge for users who prioritize this area. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Blue Prism holds an overall score of 7/10 and an ease of use score of 4/10, while IFTTT scores 6/10 overall and 10/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
18:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, both Blue Prism and IFTTT offer flexible pricing models. IFTTT stands out by offering a free plan, giving you a risk-free way to explore the platform. Blue Prism requires a paid subscription from the start."}]]}]
